item.title: What is a purple noise?
item.description: Purple noise is a variant of white noise. Purple noise is white noise (a mix of all audible frequencies) that has been filtered so that rather than having an equal representation of all frequencies, the higher frequencies are represented more than the lower ones. Is there purple noise? Blue noise is essentially the inverse of pink noise, with its amplitude increasing by 3dB per octave (the amplitude is proportional to f); and violet noise is the inverse of brown noise, with a rising response of 6dB per octave (amplitude is proportional to f squared).

Mitigation: actions taken to eliminate a hazard or reduce its potential impact. Preparedness: planning for major emergencies, including training and exercises. Response: actions taken in response to emergencies. Recovery: actions taken after a disaster to restore services and reconstruct communities.
